Text: The credit company collects the credit information from the customer, If the requested amount is greater than 1M$ an approval must be requested.
Constraints extracted: [RESPONSE(A=collect credit information from customer, B=request approval)]

Text: If the requested amount is lower or equal to 1M$ the company assess the risk of the credit.
After the assessment, if the risk is high, an approval must be requested, but if the risk is low the credit is accepted.
Constraints extracted: [RESPONSE(A=the risk is high , B=request approval), NONCOOCCURRENCE(A=the risk is high , B=the risk is low ), PRECEDENCE(A=the risk is low , B=accept credit)]

Text: After the approval request, the credit could be accepted or rejected, in both cases, an email is sent to the customer.
Constraints extracted: [PRECEDENCE(A=approval approval request, B=accept credit), PRECEDENCE(A=approval approval request, B=reject credit), PRECEDENCE(A=approval approval request, B=send case)]
